properties.areaDesc: Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 10 at 4:39PM MST until February 12 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 65 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
County.

* WHEN...From Tuesday afternoon through late Tuesday night.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation interests. Light weight and
high profile vehicles including those towing camper trailers
stand a high risk of blow offs or blowovers. Travel could be
difficult especially for lightweight, high profile vehicles and
campers.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM TUESDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE TUESDAY NIGHT
